[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    38[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mScope each Lambda's IAM role to the specific resource ARNs it touches. The tutorial-level permissions above are fine for learning and will fail any serious IAM review. The channel-entry Lambda has scoped Connect read for caller metadata only. The crisis-detector Lambda has the smallest possible permission scope (no PHI store reads at all; it operates on the utterance text passed in). The appointment-lookup Lambda has scoped EHR API egress and read on the patient-registry table only. The refill-request Lambda has scoped pharmacy-system access, OTP-issuance access via Pinpoint, and read-write on the identity-verification table only. Avoid wildcard actions and resources in production.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    39[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    40[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mA few things worth knowing upfront:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    41[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    42[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAudio is PHI from the moment the patient identifies themselves to the institution.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The fact that someone is calling a healthcare organization's patient line is itself protected information; the audio of the call is PHI by virtue of that association alone, in addition to whatever the patient says inside it. Encrypt at rest with KMS customer-managed keys, encrypt in transit with TLS, retention bound by an explicit privacy-officer-reviewed policy, BAAs in place for every vendor service that processes the audio.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    43[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mRecording-consent law varies by jurisdiction.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m All-party-consent states require an explicit consent disclosure before recording begins; one-party-consent states require less but most institutions still play a "this call may be recorded for quality" notice. The disclosure is the first thing the caller hears. Cross-state callers (the caller is in California, the institution is in Texas) follow the stricter of the two regimes. The demo's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mplay_consent_disclosure[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m plays a default disclosure; production looks up the caller's jurisdiction and plays the appropriate one.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    44[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mCrisis detection runs on every utterance, in parallel with intent classification.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A patient may call about an appointment and mention chest pain three turns into the call. The detector must catch that turn, not when the conversation ends. The demo runs the detector synchronously before intent classification on each utterance; production runs both in parallel and races them with a hard-interrupt callback.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    45[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mIdentity verification scales with stakes.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Anonymous lookups (facility hours) require no auth; soft-personal interactions (appointment confirmation) require caller-ID match plus DOB; PHI-disclosing interactions (refill, results) require OTP step-up. The architecture decouples the intent from the assurance requirement and steps up dynamically. The demo encodes the policy in [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mINTENT_ASSURANCE_REQUIREMENTS[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    46[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mScope containment is a clinical-safety requirement.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The LLM components in the stack are inherently disposed to attempt answers to questions they should not be answering. The runtime scope filter, the explicit out-of-scope intent handlers, the system-prompt constraints, and the Bedrock Guardrails defense-in-depth layer are the layered defenses. The demo's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mscope_filter_check[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m is illustrative; production's filter is policy-owned by the clinical-quality officer.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    47[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mCrisis detection vocabulary is a clinical-safety document, not an engineering configuration.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The keyword list, the severity tiering, the multilingual coverage, and the false-negative review program are owned by the clinical-quality officer. The engineering team implements what the clinical team specifies. The demo includes a small [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mCRISIS_KEYWORDS[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m table to show the pattern.[K
