[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    2844[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPer-Lambda IAM roles.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The demo uses a single set of mocked credentials. Production has one IAM role per Lambda (channel-entry, crisis-detector, intent-fallback, identity-verifier, OTP-issuer, appointment-lookup, refill-request, facility-info, callback-creator, warm-transfer, audit-writer), each scoped to the specific resource ARNs the Lambda touches. The crisis-detector Lambda has the smallest possible permission scope (no PHI store reads at all). The OTP-issuer Lambda has Pinpoint send rights and identity-verification table write only. The appointment-lookup Lambda has Secrets Manager read for the EHR credentials and FHIR API egress only. Wildcard actions and resources will fail any serious IAM review.[K
